  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\n\nFutures pointing lower with DOW leading the decline at -1.10% as geopolitical tensions escalate in the Strait of Hormuz. VIX spiking to 28.67 (+0.95%) signals increased volatility appetite while defensive rotation accelerates. Energy bucking the trend with XLE up 0.92% as oil supply concerns mount.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Trade Balance (12:30 ET)</strong> - Critical read on economic health amid global supply chain disruptions</li>\n<li><strong>Building Permits (12:00 ET)</strong> - Housing sector resilience test with rates still elevated</li>\n<li><strong>S&P Global PMI Final (13:45 ET)</strong> - Manufacturing strength gauge as industrial sector bleeds -1.14%</li>\n<li><strong>Pfizer earnings beat</strong> - XLV still down -0.30% despite positive pharma news, sector weakness persists</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>Iran-US escalation disrupts global trade routes. Materials (-1.36%) and Industrials (-1.14%) leading selloff suggests supply chain fears intensifying. Korean ship explosion adds fuel to fire.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\n\nClear flight to safety with Energy (+0.92%) and Tech (+0.11%) holding gains while cyclicals get hammered. Materials bleeding hardest at -1.36% followed by Industrials at -1.14% as war premium builds. Financials weakness (-0.65%) suggests rate cut expectations growing despite geopolitical tensions typically favoring hawkish Fed.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Strait of Hormuz chokepoint controls 21% of global petroleum liquids. Any sustained closure crashes global supply chains within weeks. Oil futures likely gapping higher at open.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY 715</strong> - Critical support from April lows, break targets 705 gap fill</li>\n<li><strong>VIX 30</strong> - Psychological resistance, clear break signals panic selling phase</li>\n<li><strong>XLE 95</strong> - Energy breakout level, war premium play accelerates above here</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ 670</strong> - Tech support holding for now, but volume weak on bounce attempts</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
